<div class="c2 retain-width"><p class="type">Blog Post</p></div>
<h1>Ukraine’s oligarchs are bad for democracy and economic reform</h1>
<p class="intro op-kicker">Ukraine’s late and incomplete economic reform created a class of super-wealthy oligarchs who now stand in the way of further liberalisation. The oligarchs’ oversized influence only deepens public distrust in a structurally weak political system. Nevertheless, Ukraine is making some attempts to uproot corruption and the next steps are clear.</p>
<p class="meta">
<span class="row"><span class="label">By: </span>
<a href="https://www.bruegel.org/author/marek-dabrowski/" title="Posts by Marek Dabrowski" class="author url fn" rel="author">Marek Dabrowski</a> and <a href="https://www.bruegel.org/author/admin/" title="Posts by Bruegel" class="author url fn" rel="author">Bruegel</a></span>
<span class="row"><span class="label">Date: </span>October 3, 2017</span>
<span class="row"><span class="label">Topic: </span>European Macroeconomics &amp; Governance</span>
<span class="Social is-mobile">
<span class="Social-item" data-name="tw">
<svg class="Social-icon Social-icon-default">
<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="https://www.bruegel.org/wp-content/themes/bruegel/ui/design/graphics/sprite.svg#twitter"></use>
</svg>
</span>
<span class="Social-item" data-name="fb">
<svg class="Social-icon Social-icon-default">
<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="https://www.bruegel.org/wp-content/themes/bruegel/ui/design/graphics/sprite.svg#facebook"></use>
</svg>
</span>
<span class="Social-item" data-name="in">
<svg class="Social-icon Social-icon-default">
<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="https://www.bruegel.org/wp-content/themes/bruegel/ui/design/graphics/sprite.svg#linkedin"></use>
</svg>
</span>
<span class="Social-item">
<svg class="Social-icon Social-icon-default">
<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="https://www.bruegel.org/wp-content/themes/bruegel/ui/design/graphics/sprite.svg#mail"></use>
</svg>
</span>
</span>
</p>
<div class="body u-posRelative">
<ul class="Social is-scrolled u-cf">
<li class="Social-item" data-name="tw">
<svg class="Social-icon Social-icon-default">
<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="https://www.bruegel.org/wp-content/themes/bruegel/ui/design/graphics/sprite.svg#twitter"></use>
</svg>
<svg class="Social-icon Social-icon-hover">
<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="https://www.bruegel.org/wp-content/themes/bruegel/ui/design/graphics/sprite.svg#twitterhover"></use>
</svg>
</li>
<li class="Social-item" data-name="fb">
<svg class="Social-icon Social-icon-default">
<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="https://www.bruegel.org/wp-content/themes/bruegel/ui/design/graphics/sprite.svg#facebook"></use>
</svg>
<svg class="Social-icon Social-icon-hover">
