<h2>Covid-19 and emerging economies: What to expect in the short- and medium-term</h2>
<p class="intro">This article was originally published in the Observer Research Foundation. As Brazil, Russia, India and Mexico record the fast spread of the Covid-19 contagion, a third wave of the pandemic is reaching the emerging world. As a result, business sentiment has decreased in March and April in the region. What’s more, as emerging economies gradually [&hellip;]</p>
<div class="meta">
<span class="row"><span class="label">By: </span>Alicia García-Herrero</span>
<span class="row"><span class="label">Topic: </span>Global Economics &amp; Governance</span>
